title: Les Claypool's Frog Brigade - Animals (Live) 2001 320ak
description:
Colonel Les Claypool's Fearless Flying Frog Brigade (also known as The Les Claypool Frog Brigade) is one of many musical projects involving Primus bassist Les Claypool. The original band was formed in summer 2000 and consisted of: Les Claypool (bass, vocals), Todd Huth (guitars, vocals), Jay Lane (drums), Jeff Chimenti (keyboards), Skerik (saxophone), and Eenor (guitars, cÃƒÂ¼mbÃƒÂ¼Ã…Å¸). Les Claypool has described their sound as, "It's kind of a King Crimson meets Pink Floyd meets Frank Zappa type thing."

Les Claypool's Frog Brigade released on July 24, 2001  a live cover of Pink Floyd Animals. 
The album is a performance of the Pink Floyd studio album Animals. It is introduced as "more Pink Floyd than any human being should ever withstand"
